History of Present Illness:
Ms. ___ is a ___ right-handdominant ___ woman who 
had a mechanical slip and fall on ___.  At that 
time, she fell down a flight of stairs and sustained a left 
proximal humerus fracture.  Initially seen at ___, 
she was diagnosed with a proximal humerus fracture, was  
subsequently referred to your attention.  Seen and evaluated in 
the office, she demonstrated a displaced proximal humerus 
fracture and was referred to my attention out of concernfor 
surgical intervention.

She explains she is having ongoing pain and bruising.  She has 
been wearing her sling for comfort.  She denies any numbness or 
tingling.  She had no prior history of left-sided shoulder pain.

 
Past Medical History:
1. Hyperlipidemia
2. GERD
